2011-10-20:
-----------

* Passage à NSP

* scicoslab-devel mailing liste

* Licence:
  -> NSP is under BSD license (and also GPL according to the user will)
  -> Scicos is BSD license for the most part with additional closed source parts
     BSD parts:
       - graphical editor
       - block library
       - code generator
       - matronly (matrila ?) implementation

     Closed source parts:
       - Scicos related toolboxes as the import simulink program
       - Scicos compiler and Scicos simulator

* semantics of blocks: start from a simple sub-set of blocks, small enough to
  give a true semantics (in the mathematical sense) static (typing rules) and
  dynamic (evaluation rules (operational semantics) or mathematical meaning
  (denotational semantics)

* simulink translator: implement the rest of basic blocks, try to get some
  useful input from other developers ?

* matexp: "matrice expression" embedded language -> matronly or matrila.


